<paragraph id="E51836F2EA0D617244F8F49BFF01FDEA" blockId="12.[178,1085,355,571]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Body length 
<quantity id="225F9B17EA0D61724655F49BFD73FE13" box="[543,665,429,451]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.8">2.8-3.2 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="7D9C2A77EA0D6172477DF49BFC6EFE12" box="[823,900,429,451]" captionStart="Figs 24-31" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1410,1430]" captionTargetBox="[181,1080,219,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-130@13.[178,1085,219,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 24-31: Geostiba erecta nov.sp. (24-26, 28-30: holotype): (24) male habitus; (25-26) male forebody in dorsal and in ventral view; (27) female forebody; (28) male abdomen; (29) male tergites VI-VIII in lateral view; (30) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (31) spermatheca. Scale bars: 24: 1.0 mm; 25-29: 0.5 mm; 30-31: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
. Coloration: head dark-brown to blackish; pronotum and elytra reddish to dark-brown; abdomen brown, with segments VI-VII dark-brown, or completely dark-brown to blackish-brown; legs yellowish; antennae brown to dark-brown, usually with antennomeres I-II at least slightly paler.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51836F2EA0D617244F8F77DFD4CFD4C" blockId="12.[178,1085,587,669]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">
Head 1.00-1.09 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation id="7D9C2A77EA0D6172461BF77DFD24FDB0" box="[593,718,587,609]" captionStart="Figs 24-31" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1410,1430]" captionTargetBox="[181,1080,219,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-130@13.[178,1085,219,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 24-31: Geostiba erecta nov.sp. (24-26, 28-30: holotype): (24) male habitus; (25-26) male forebody in dorsal and in ventral view; (27) female forebody; (28) male abdomen; (29) male tergites VI-VIII in lateral view; (30) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (31) spermatheca. Scale bars: 24: 1.0 mm; 25-29: 0.5 mm; 30-31: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Figs 25, 27</figureCitation>
); punctation extremely fine, barely noticeable; surface with very shallow microreticulation. Eyes relatively small, 0.30-0.45 times as long as postocular region in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51836F2EA0D617244F8F798FDCFFCCF" blockId="12.[178,1085,685,798]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">
Pronotum without apparent sexual dimorphism (
<figureCitation id="7D9C2A77EA0D617246EDF79BFCCBFD12" box="[679,801,685,707]" captionStart="Figs 24-31" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1410,1430]" captionTargetBox="[181,1080,219,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-130@13.[178,1085,219,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 24-31: Geostiba erecta nov.sp. (24-26, 28-30: holotype): (24) male habitus; (25-26) male forebody in dorsal and in ventral view; (27) female forebody; (28) male abdomen; (29) male tergites VI-VIII in lateral view; (30) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (31) spermatheca. Scale bars: 24: 1.0 mm; 25-29: 0.5 mm; 30-31: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Figs 25, 27</figureCitation>
), approximately 1.05 times as wide as long, posterior margin in both sexes weakly and broadly convex, in the middle almost truncate; punctation extremely fine, barely noticeable; microreticulation somewhat more distinct than that of head.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51836F2EA0D617244F8F618FC99FC51" blockId="12.[178,1084,814,896]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">
Elytra with moderately pronounced sexual dimorphism, 0.6-0.7 times as long as pronotum (
<figureCitation id="7D9C2A77EA0D617244A1F67AFE81FCB3" box="[235,363,844,866]" captionStart="Figs 24-31" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1410,1430]" captionTargetBox="[181,1080,219,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-130@13.[178,1085,219,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 24-31: Geostiba erecta nov.sp. (24-26, 28-30: holotype): (24) male habitus; (25-26) male forebody in dorsal and in ventral view; (27) female forebody; (28) male abdomen; (29) male tergites VI-VIII in lateral view; (30) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (31) spermatheca. Scale bars: 24: 1.0 mm; 25-29: 0.5 mm; 30-31: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Figs 25, 27</figureCitation>
); punctation in both sexes fine, not granulose; microsculpture very shallow, less pronounced than that of pronotum. Hind wings reduced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51836F2EA0D617244F8F6A6FCF5FBD1" blockId="12.[178,1085,912,1024]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="7D9C2A77EA0D61724569F6A6FE84FC77" box="[291,366,912,934]" captionStart="Figs 24-31" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1410,1430]" captionTargetBox="[181,1080,219,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-130@13.[178,1085,219,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 24-31: Geostiba erecta nov.sp. (24-26, 28-30: holotype): (24) male habitus; (25-26) male forebody in dorsal and in ventral view; (27) female forebody; (28) male abdomen; (29) male tergites VI-VIII in lateral view; (30) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (31) spermatheca. Scale bars: 24: 1.0 mm; 25-29: 0.5 mm; 30-31: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) usually at least slightly wider than elytra; punctation moderately fine and sparse; microreticulation distinct; posterior margin of tergite VII usually with narrow rudiment of a palisade fringe; tergites IV and V without, VII with sexual dimorphism; posterior margin of tergite VIII weakly convex in both sexes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51836F2EA0D617244F8F139FBF9FB50" blockId="12.[178,1085,1039,1153]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">
Ƌ (with fully developed secondary sexual characters): elytra with pair of erect tubercles near apex of scutellum (
<figureCitation id="7D9C2A77EA0D617245E0F118FE1DFB95" box="[426,503,1070,1092]" captionStart="Figs 24-31" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1410,1430]" captionTargetBox="[181,1080,219,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-130@13.[178,1085,219,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 24-31: Geostiba erecta nov.sp. (24-26, 28-30: holotype): (24) male habitus; (25-26) male forebody in dorsal and in ventral view; (27) female forebody; (28) male abdomen; (29) male tergites VI-VIII in lateral view; (30) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (31) spermatheca. Scale bars: 24: 1.0 mm; 25-29: 0.5 mm; 30-31: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
), surface without distinct impressions; abdominal tergite VII with long, slender, remarkably erect, and apically acute spine-like process at posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="7D9C2A77EA0D61724566F15DFE9FFB50" box="[300,373,1131,1153]" captionStart="Figs 24-31" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1410,1430]" captionTargetBox="[181,1080,219,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-130@13.[178,1085,219,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 24-31: Geostiba erecta nov.sp. (24-26, 28-30: holotype): (24) male habitus; (25-26) male forebody in dorsal and in ventral view; (27) female forebody; (28) male abdomen; (29) male tergites VI-VIII in lateral view; (30) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (31) spermatheca. Scale bars: 24: 1.0 mm; 25-29: 0.5 mm; 30-31: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); median lobe of aedeagus with very slender cristal process (
<figureCitation id="7D9C2A77EA0D617247F5F15DFBEDFB50" box="[959,1031,1131,1153]" captionStart="Figs 24-31" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1410,1430]" captionTargetBox="[181,1080,219,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-130@13.[178,1085,219,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 24-31: Geostiba erecta nov.sp. (24-26, 28-30: holotype): (24) male habitus; (25-26) male forebody in dorsal and in ventral view; (27) female forebody; (28) male abdomen; (29) male tergites VI-VIII in lateral view; (30) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (31) spermatheca. Scale bars: 24: 1.0 mm; 25-29: 0.5 mm; 30-31: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51836F2EA0D617244F8F1A2FDA4FB77" blockId="12.[178,1085,1168,1257]" box="[178,590,1168,1195]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">
<specimenCount id="F3A1FD7BEA0D617244F8F1A2FF2AFB7A" box="[178,192,1172,1195]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: spermatheca not distinctive (
<figureCitation id="7D9C2A77EA0D617245BDF1A6FDA8FB77" box="[503,578,1168,1190]" captionStart="Figs 24-31" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1410,1430]" captionTargetBox="[181,1080,219,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-130@13.[178,1085,219,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 24-31: Geostiba erecta nov.sp. (24-26, 28-30: holotype): (24) male habitus; (25-26) male forebody in dorsal and in ventral view; (27) female forebody; (28) male abdomen; (29) male tergites VI-VIII in lateral view; (30) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (31) spermatheca. Scale bars: 24: 1.0 mm; 25-29: 0.5 mm; 30-31: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51836F2EA0D617244F8F180FCCCFB38" blockId="12.[178,1085,1168,1257]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">E t y m o l o g y: The name (Latin, adjective) alludes to the erect tubercles on the male elytra and the erect process of the male abdominal tergite VII.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51836F2EA0D617244F8F1CEFCEFF9C7" blockId="12.[178,1085,1272,1558]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s: Using the key in 
<bibRefCitation id="81364B03EA0D6172469FF1CEFC95FADF" author="ASSING V" box="[725,895,1272,1294]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" pagination="903 - 1006" refId="ref43550" refString="ASSING V. (2005 a): A revision of the species of Geostiba THOMSON and Tropimenelytron PACE of the Eastern Mediterranean, the Caucasus, and adjacent regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 37 (2): 903 - 1006." type="journal article" year="2005">ASSING (2005a)</bibRefCitation>
, the new species would key out at couplets 84-86, together with the geographically close 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D617247F5F023FECEFA98" authority="PACE 1983" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D617247F5F023FBD7FAFA" box="[959,1085,1301,1323]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. simulans</emphasis>
PACE 1983
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="9DB07662EA0D6172457FF005FE9CFA98" box="[309,374,1331,1353]" name="Turkey" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Hatay</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D617245C7F005FD4EFA98" authority="ASSING 2004" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2004" box="[397,676,1331,1353]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marasica">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D617245C7F005FDE5FA98" box="[397,527,1331,1353]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. marasica</emphasis>
ASSING 2004
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion id="2763F810EA0D617246FFF005FCB6FA99" box="[693,860,1331,1353]" country="Turkey" name="Kahramanmaras" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Kahramanmaraş</collectingRegion>
), 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D6172473CF005FF0FFAB7" authority="ASSING 2003" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamata">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D6172473CF005FC0FFA98" box="[886,997,1331,1353]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. hamata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="81364B03EA0D617247BAF005FF0FFAB7" author="ASSING V" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" pagination="103 - 129" refId="ref43427" refString="ASSING V. (2003): A revision of the species of Geostiba THOMSON of the Eastern Mediterranean. VI. (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 35 (1): 103 - 129." type="journal article" year="2003">ASSING 2003</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="9DB07662EA0D617244B8F066FED9FAB7" box="[242,307,1360,1382]" name="Turkey" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Hatay</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D6172453BF066FD8DFAB7" authority="ASSING 2004" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2004" box="[369,615,1360,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adunca">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D6172453BF066FE30FAB7" box="[369,474,1360,1382]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. adunca</emphasis>
ASSING 2004
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion id="2763F810EA0D6172463EF066FCF1FAB7" box="[628,795,1360,1382]" country="Turkey" name="Kahramanmaras" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">Kahramanmaraş</collectingRegion>
). It is distinguished from all these species particularly by the erect tubercles on the male elytra, as well as by the shape of the process of the male tergite VII. It is additionally separated from 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D6172478EF0BCFBD7FA71" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1983" box="[964,1085,1418,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D6172478EF0BCFBD7FA71" box="[964,1085,1418,1440]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. simulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D617244AAF09EFE8BFA6F" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2004" box="[224,353,1448,1470]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marasica">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D617244AAF09EFE8BFA6F" box="[224,353,1448,1470]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. marasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of a dimorphism of the male pronotum and from 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D6172406EF09EFF14FA0A" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamata">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D6172406EF09EFF14FA0A" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. hamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D61724565F0F3FE72FA0A" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2004" box="[303,408,1477,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adunca">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D61724565F0F3FE72FA0A" box="[303,408,1477,1499]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. adunca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the short and very slender cristal process of the median lobe of the aedeagus. For illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D61724644F0D4FD63FA29" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1983" box="[526,649,1506,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D61724644F0D4FD63FA29" box="[526,649,1506,1528]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. simulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D617246D2F0D4FCF2FA29" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2004" box="[664,792,1506,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marasica">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D617246D2F0D4FCF2FA29" box="[664,792,1506,1528]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. marasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D6172476DF0D4FC7EFA29" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2003" box="[807,916,1506,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamata">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D6172476DF0D4FC7EFA29" box="[807,916,1506,1528]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. hamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="22A74D71EA0D6172479BF0D4FBD6FA29" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2004" box="[977,1084,1506,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adunca">
<emphasis id="D7D3EAE0EA0D6172479BF0D4FBD6FA29" box="[977,1084,1506,1528]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203">G. adunca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="81364B03EA0D61724492F336FE8EF9C7" author="PACE R" box="[216,356,1536,1558]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" pagination="3 - 46" refId="ref43801" refString="PACE R. (1983 b): Specie del genere Geostiba THOMSON raccolte dal Dr. C. Besuchet e collaboratori in Marocco, nella Penisola Iberica e Balcanica, e nel Medio Oriente (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue suisse de Zoologie 90: 3 - 46." type="journal article" year="1983">PACE (1983b)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="81364B03EA0D617245DCF336FDCCF9C7" author="ASSING V" box="[406,550,1536,1558]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" pagination="103 - 129" refId="ref43427" refString="ASSING V. (2003): A revision of the species of Geostiba THOMSON of the Eastern Mediterranean. VI. (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 35 (1): 103 - 129." type="journal article" year="2003">ASSING (2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="81364B03EA0D6172467AF336FD9BF9C7" author="ASSING V" box="[560,625,1536,1558]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1203" pagination="615 - 638" refId="ref43470" refString="ASSING V. (2004 a): A revision of the Turkish species of Geostiba THOMSON. V. New species and additional records (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 36 (2): 615 - 638." type="journal article" year="2004">2004a</bibRefCitation>
), respectively.
